The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Match on
                                                                                                               Match on
                            
	The sports ministry has said India and Pakistan should play, not fight in response to a question whether the no-cricket policy with Islamabad after the Mumbai attacks has changed.        
	Asked about the T20 World Cup that includes matches between India and Pakistan, foreign minister S.M. Krishna said: It has to be dealt with by the sports ministry.        
	Sports minister M.S. Gill said: The match is on (referring to Wednesdays warm-up).... It is good as we should play and not fight.                                                                                                                                                                           
